VALUES ('7377abc7-757a-4515-a3a4-402b249ccd2c', 'Which choice best states the main idea of the text?', 'Within quantum biology, the recovery of a suppressed dissenting tradition has long been read as straightforward progress, a reading that a network of amateurs—whose archives, only recently catalogued, complicate the received chronology—did much to entrench. What that account treats as decoherence, however, the observed regularity reframes: the apparent advance, far from being intrinsic, was conditioned by an institutional tunnelling that the standard narrative cannot model. Granting that the correlation is genuine, one must still resist the inference that it is causal, for the same configuration recurs except in the cases its own framework cannot index.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"Read as a whole, the passage advances a qualified central claim. The opening impression of straightforward progress is, in fact, the passage''s settled thesis —as the nested concession ultimately reveals.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[False Lead] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"B","text":"Read as a whole, the passage advances a qualified central claim. A documented correlation is real but not causal, since the same pattern recurs where the supposed mechanism is absent —as the nested concession ultimately reveals.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: its second sentence is the only one that satisfies the discriminating condition."},{"id":"C","text":"Read as a whole, the passage advances a qualified central claim. Because the pattern is causal, the institutional condition it produces must be its effect rather than its source —as the nested concession ultimately reveals.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Reciprocal Error] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"D","text":"Read as a whole, the passage advances a qualified central claim. No correlation of this kind can ever, in any field, license a causal inference —as the nested concession ultimately reveals.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Over-Extrapolation] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Logical Reconstruction:
