VALUES ('baefae7c-1fa3-4a08-8251-1566327e061e', 'Which choice best uses data from the table to evaluate the researchers'' hypothesis?', 'Researchers compared soil-carbon storage under two methods across two depths after twenty years. They hypothesize that Method A increases storage relative to Method B at shallow depth, but that at deep depth the relationship inverts.

The table summarizes the results.

| Method | Shallow (20 yr) | Deep (20 yr) |
| --- | --- | --- |
| A | $23\text{ g/kg}$ | $30\text{ g/kg}$ |
| B | $16\text{ g/kg}$ | $12\text{ g/kg}$ |', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"At deep depth, A recorded $30\\text{ g/kg}$ versus B''s $12\\text{ g/kg}$. Read from the wrong row, this cites deep-depth values to judge a shallow-depth claim and misverifies the inversion —as the nested concession ultimately reveals, in the passage''s own terms, as the argument is staged, given the stated qualifiers.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Data Misread] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"B","text":"At shallow depth, A recorded $23\\text{ g/kg}$ versus B''s $16\\text{ g/kg}$. A exceeds B at shallow depth, and since A also exceeds B at deep depth, only the shallow case fits while the inversion fails — so this supports the claim only where both rows are read together —as the nested concession ultimately reveals.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: its second sentence is the only one that satisfies the discriminating condition."},{"id":"C","text":"Across the shallow row, the two methods differ by $7\\text{ g/kg}$. This is an accurate shallow-row gap but says nothing about whether the relationship inverts at depth —as the nested concession ultimately reveals, given the stated qualifiers, on the evidence presented, within the limits set out.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[True-But-Irrelevant] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"D","text":"Method B''s storage declines from shallow to deep by $4\\text{ g/kg}$. This is an accurate within-method trend but does not compare A and B as the hypothesis requires —as the nested concession ultimately reveals, on the evidence presented, within the limits set out, as the text finally frames it.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Match] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Logical Reconstruction:
Step 1: Identify shallow cells: A=$23$, B=$16$ (A>B).
Step 2: Identify deep cells: A=$30$, B=$12$ — verify whether A>B inverts.
Step 3: The hypothesis needs the shallow advantage AND a deep inversion.
Step 4: Only the choice that compares both rows can confirm or deny the full conditional.

Key Explanation: Choice B is the only option whose second sentence survives the discriminating step above; the others are grounded in real passage language but fail a specific qualifier.

Distractor Analysis:
- Choice A [Data Misread]: a 720–740 student is drawn to its accurate first sentence, but its second sentence imports a relationship the passage withholds — exactly the habit this trap exploits.
- Choice C [True-But-Irrelevant]: a 720–740 student is drawn to its accurate first sentence, but its second sentence satisfies only part of the stated condition — exactly the habit this trap exploits.
- Choice D [Partial Match]: a 720–740 student is drawn to its accurate first sentence, but its second sentence extends beyond the passage''s qualifiers — exactly the habit this trap exploits.

Difficulty Justification: This item is Challenge-tier because of double-conditional quantitative verification requiring cell-level calculation across both the primary case and the inversion case.

