VALUES ('4886f364-3006-48dc-b626-eb8ac5a2eb03', 'Which choice completes the text so that it conforms to the conventions of Standard English?', 'The monograph''s central term—decoherence, a coinage its author, a notoriously precise stylist, defended at length—anchors the argument ______ that the later commentators, working from an abridged edition, persistently misread.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":", a claim","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Comma Splice] A surface-plausible mark that either splices independent clauses or mislocates the appositive boundary."},{"id":"B","text":": a claim","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: the boundary correctly attaches the non-restrictive appositive without splicing the clause."},{"id":"C","text":"; a claim","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Restrictive/Non-Restrictive] A surface-plausible mark that either splices independent clauses or mislocates the appositive boundary."},{"id":"D","text":" a claim","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Comma Splice] A surface-plausible mark that either splices independent clauses or mislocates the appositive boundary."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Logical Reconstruction:
