VALUES ('6d69fdf1-b9e1-43e0-8a86-2757e910c0bf', 'The student wants to contrast Methods X and Y, highlight their shared objective, and frame the comparison as a defense of X''s earlier timeline. Which choice best accomplishes this goal?', '• Method X was developed in quantum biology a decade before Method Y.
• Method X and Method Y share the objective of reducing measurement bias.
• Method Y is faster but assumes conditions X does not require.
• A 2021 review found X more robust under sparse data.
• Both methods were first applied to archival samples.
• Critics initially dismissed X as impractical.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"Both X and Y aim to reduce measurement bias, though they differ in their assumptions. Because Y is faster, the comparison shows Y to be the superior successor in every respect.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Goal Under-Specification] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"B","text":"Both X and Y aim to reduce measurement bias, though they differ in their assumptions. Because X preceded Y and proves more robust under sparse data, the comparison can be framed as a defense of X''s earlier timeline.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: its second sentence is the only one that satisfies the discriminating condition."},{"id":"C","text":"Both X and Y aim to reduce measurement bias, though they differ in their assumptions. Because critics dismissed X, the comparison establishes that X was ultimately impractical, given the stated qualifiers.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Goal Under-Specification] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"D","text":"Method Y is faster than X and was applied to archival samples. Both were first applied to archival samples, which settles the question of priority, on the evidence presented, within the limits set out.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[True-But-Irrelevant] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Logical Reconstruction:
