VALUES ('91b07b27-19af-40e1-9248-090131027985', 'Which choice completes the text so that it conforms to the conventions of Standard English?', 'Neither the founder''s voluminous correspondence nor the institutional ledgers that, catalogued only recently by archivists in archaeology, corroborate the legend ______ free of the embellishment that later hagiography supplied.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"remain","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Proximity Decoy] Agrees with the nearest plural noun in the intervening relative clause rather than the true correlative subject."},{"id":"B","text":"remaining","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Proximity Decoy] Agrees with the nearest plural noun in the intervening relative clause rather than the true correlative subject."},{"id":"C","text":"remains","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: with a neither/nor subject the verb agrees with the nearer singular element, and the inverted clause requires the singular present."},{"id":"D","text":"to remain","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Proximity Decoy] Agrees with the nearest plural noun in the intervening relative clause rather than the true correlative subject."}]'::jsonb, 'C', 'Logical Reconstruction:
